BRISTOL-MYERS SQUIBB Co. (New York) -- Gerald C. Beddall, 47 years old, was named president of the Clairol division of this pharmaceuticals and health-care company.
He succeeds C. Benjamin Brooks Jr., who will retire Nov. 1.
Mr. Brooks declined to give his age, but he said his leaving is a normal retirement.
Mr. Beddall had been executive vice president of the division since April.
Clairol, which makes hair and skin products, was a division of Bristol-Myers Co. before that company's merger with Squibb Corp. 

